In this video, we will understand how to extract meaningful information from satellite data.
So far, we’ve been visualizing maps like RGB and NDVI using leaflet. But in real-world applications, we need to know about numerical insights.

In this video, you will learn:

✔ What is reduceRegion() in Google Earth Engine
✔ How pixel values are converted into statistics like mean NDVI
✔ How to upload a custom Region of Interest (ROI) using GeoJSON
✔ How frontend and backend interact in a WebGIS system
✔ How results are displayed dynamically in the browser

We also extend WebGIS application, where users can upload their own ROI and analyze satellite data interactively.

This is a key concept for building real-world geospatial applications.

👉 In the next video, we will explore time-series analysis and export results as CSV.
